Barn: Claes f. 42. — Stud:ex. i Saltsjöbaden 31, civ:ing:ex. v. KTH 35, Höh. Fach-schule f. Textilind. i Aachen 37-38. Anst. v. Sv. translated: Lagnell, Emil Gunnar, civil engineer, Borås, b. 23/4/13 in Stockholm to comrade Emil Bernhard L. and Margareta Andersson. M. Birgit Hansson. Children: Claes b. 42. - Graduated from Saltsjöbaden High School in 1931, graduated as a civil engineer from the Royal Institute of Technology in 1935, attended Höhere Fachschule f. Textilindustrie in Aachen from 1937-1938. Employed by Swedish Wool Consortium A-B in Borås since 1935, currently serving as production technical manager and assistant director. Member of the Swedish Technical Association since 1935.
